part.Short:
A bowed lune is cracked from where it was smashed off the gallium lathe. The shedim had no eyes left to color the dim and final Face, and it lay too long discarded in a pool of warm static. The sultanate is broken, and in its interregnum a great variety of morbid symptoms have appeared.

In ageless blood, a single phrase has been smeared onto its surface by a shivering hand:

{{r|"FORGIVE ME"}}
